  "text": "The CODEOWNERS infrastructure in grafana/grafana spans 10 files across 4 layers:\n\n1. **Ownership Definition**: .github/CODEOWNERS defines GitHub code ownership rules, mapping directory patterns to team handles for automatic PR review assignment.\n\n2. **CI Validation**: .github/workflows/codeowners-validator.yml runs a GitHub Actions workflow that validates the CODEOWNERS file syntax and ensures all referenced teams exist.\n\n3. **Manifest Generation** (JavaScript): The scripts/codeowners-manifest/ directory contains 6 JavaScript files that parse, index, and generate a structured manifest from the CODEOWNERS file:\n   - index.js: Entry point that orchestrates the generation pipeline\n   - generate.js: Core generation logic\n   - raw.js: Raw CODEOWNERS file parser\n   - constants.js: Shared constants (team names, path patterns)\n   - metadata.js: Enriches parsed entries with team metadata\n   - utils.js: Shared utility functions\n\n4. **Go Integration**: pkg/services/featuremgmt/codeowners.go defines codeowner constants that map feature flags to owning teams. pkg/services/featuremgmt/models.go defines the data model that links features to their codeowner teams, enabling runtime ownership queries.",
